---
description: Web accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA) compliance and best practices for inclusive design.
alwaysApply: false
---
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible.
- Use proper ARIA labels and roles for complex UI components.
- Implement proper focus management and visible focus indicators.
- Use semantic HTML elements for proper document structure.
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text).
- Provide alternative text for all images and media content.
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6) for content organization.
- Implement proper form labels and error messaging.
- Use proper table markup with headers and captions.
- Ensure proper screen reader compatibility for all content.
- Implement proper skip navigation links for keyboard users.
- Use proper language attributes for international content.
- Ensure proper timeouts and user control for auto-updating content.
- Implement proper error prevention and recovery mechanisms.
- Use proper motion and animation preferences (prefers-reduced-motion).
